<anchor xml:id="_class_d__byte_1a44c680fdbd37f664c263f2115337d21a"/><section>
    <title>R_bytef()</title>
<indexterm><primary>R_bytef</primary><secondary>D_byte</secondary></indexterm>
<indexterm><primary>D_byte</primary><secondary>R_bytef</secondary></indexterm>
<para><computeroutput>int D_byte::R_bytef ( )</computeroutput></para>
<para>return input bits from last read. Bits are shifted and re-ordered to match the output bits. This means that the bit for switch 1 and led 1 use the same mask. </para>
</section>
